Package net.firstpartners.data

Classes to hold Table Data Terminology is similar to MS Excel - Ranges (named groups of Cells) and Cells. Since we also map from other sources into these classes, they could contain info from other sources e.g. a Word Document. Classes in this package are the only ones injected into the Working Knowledge of the Rule Engine
Since:
1.0
Version:
1.1
Author:
pbrowne
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cell
    JavaBean equivalent of a cell in an Excel Spreadsheet.
    Range
    A range is just a holder for a group of named cells - maps to a similar Concept in MS Excel We use it as a convenience for loading our values into working memory Since we also map from other sources into these classes, a Range could contain one table from a Word Document.
    RangeList
    Holder of all multiple Named Ranges from a spreadsheet.
